The paper is about an automated theorem prover that uses machine learning to select appropriate tactics for proving theorems. This falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the performance of the prover suggests that it could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of the prover on top of an interactive theorem prover, which could place it under programming languages (cs.PL) or software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of Monte Carlo tree search in the algorithm suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG).
